    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <hi rend="underline">In haste</hi>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <placeName>Buff Bay</placeName>
                <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June 37</date>
            </p>
            <p>Reverend Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Since closing your letter, which I here send you, I reced<lb/> a
                letter from our friend <persName>M Peixotto</persName>, with yours enclosed
                bearing<lb/> date <date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May</date>, by which I was glad to
                hear you were well &amp; hearty.<lb/> I have long ere this released you of any blame
                respecting<lb/> the tuition of my Brother in Law, &amp; <sic>Iam</sic> almost
                satisfied<lb/> that I shall sufficiently satisfy my Father's Son, that the<lb/>
                fault lays with the unaccountable eccentricities of<lb/> my friend <persName>Mr
                    P.</persName> But it is hard that you should be blamed<lb/> for this, &amp;
                rather than an honest declaration, that you<lb/> should be spoken of in such a way,
                as <del>to</del> would tend to<lb/> show that your religious feeling is not of that
                kind it ought<lb/> to be. Alas! I know the sting of <sic>persicution</sic> &amp;
                sarcasms too<lb/>
                <add>?</add> to swallow all such <sic>indigestable</sic> matter! You are<lb/>
                <add>?</add> &amp; where my voice can declare it, believe me<lb/> despite of malice,
                I will echo the truth, let the result be<lb/> what it may. I know too well your
                trouble &amp; labor;<lb/> I have I believe spoken to you of your several works; in the<lb/>
                <sic>inclosed</sic> letter, therefore have not much more to say—only<lb/> God speed
                you in your exertions for our good.<lb/> I thought the <persName>Revd M
                    Nathan</persName> had long paid—But I will<lb/> not omit asking in plain
                English, for he does not seem<lb/> to understand <hi rend="underline">hints</hi>, it
                is too bad, But I will <add>?</add> him 'till he pays.<lb/> Excuse my detaining you
                so long <del>for</del> with the amount of<lb/> your Books, but I could not write
                before this.<lb/> God <add>?</add> you, &amp; give you the desires of<lb/> your
                heart for good—is the wish of</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">your dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">W W Sollas</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
